The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE VCD 

 (MusicWorld, Rs 299) This Ritwik Ghatak classic traces the life of a lower-middle 

class girl?s fight against the socio-economic pressures that cripple her and her 

family. The film, described by Ghatak as his creative best, stars Supriya Chowdhury 

and Anil Chattopadhyay. 

THE DISPLAY

 (CIMA Gallery, till April 2, 2 pm-7 pm ? from 3 pm on Mondays) The exhibition 

focuses on the artists who turned to their roots to forge a relationship between 

the traditional and the modern. The display showcases the works of Haku Shah, 

Vaikuntam, Ramananda Bandopadhyay, Jyoti Bhatt and Lalu Prosad Shaw.

 THE SHOW

(Tollygunge Club, 7 pm, March 26) The event conceptualised by Sujoy Prosad Chatterjee 

features actress Rupa Ganguly , singer Usha Uthup, and theatre artistes Bijoylakshmi 

Burman and Poonam Singh in a melange of music and enactment. 




